  /- (by claude) Step 34: Establish the key intermediate bound.

     We use the following chain of inequalities:

     ∏_j det(A_j)^{q_j}
       ≤ ∏_j [(d/α_j²)^{m_j} × q_j^{-m_j} × ∏_{i∈I_j} λ_i]^{q_j}  (Hadamard)
       = d^{∑_j q_j m_j} × ∏_j α_j^{-2 q_j m_j} × ∏_j q_j^{-q_j m_j} × ∏_j (∏_{i∈I_j} λ_i)^{q_j}
       = d^{Ac} × ∏_j α_j^{-2 q_j m_j} × ∏_j q_j^{-q_j m_j} × ∏_j (∏_{i∈I_j} λ_i)^{q_j}

     Then by h_eigenvalue_telescoping:
       ∏_j (∏_{i∈I_j} λ_i)^{q_j} ≤ λ₁^{Ac-d+β} × λ_d^{-β} × det(M)

     Combining and using eigenvalue-to-norm bounds:
       ≤ d^{Ac} × ∏_j α_j^{-2 q_j m_j} × ∏_j q_j^{-q_j m_j} × ‖M_max‖^{Ac-d+β} × ‖T⁻¹‖^β × det(M)

     This is the FULL exponent bound. The goal requires the HALVED exponent bound,
     which is sqrt of this. For this to hold, we need the full-exponent coefficient
